==English==
===Etymology===
The usage of this idiom began in the second half of the 1900's.

===Idiom===
'''[[price]] [[is]] [[right]]'''
# {{idiom}} The [[cost]] of a thing is [[reasonable]] and of [[good]] [[value]].
#: ''The '''price is right''' for this used [[car]].

===Usage note===
The idiom the 'price is right' can often be used for something that is [[free]], but is [[junk]] or [[impractical]]. <br />
''The car the Smiths [[give|gave]] me for Christmas is junky and dangerous; but the price is right.''